						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is damaged. It seems to record a tax-free gift of land made by the <hi rend="italic">Sabhā</hi> of the place (purpose not clear) at the request of Kōrai Śēndaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kēraḷādityadēva of Kuḍamaṅgalam in Malaimaṇḍalam who is stated to be a local officer at Māṉanilainallūr in Kaḷakkuḍi-nāḍu, for the welfare of Buddattiruvaḍi of Tiruppāppūr. </p>						

						</summary>
